      • getNoRxLoss

        public java.lang.Boolean getNoRxLoss()
        Flag that enables optimized data transfer over the pipe. When the value is true, the host buffers data to prevent data overrun. This allows the virtual machine to read all of the data transferred over the pipe with no data loss. This property is optional and it is only relevant when the value of getType() is one of SerialTypes.BackingType.PIPE_SERVER or SerialTypes.BackingType.PIPE_CLIENT.
        Returns:
        The current value of the property.

      • setNoRxLoss

        public void setNoRxLoss(java.lang.Boolean noRxLoss)
        Flag that enables optimized data transfer over the pipe. When the value is true, the host buffers data to prevent data overrun. This allows the virtual machine to read all of the data transferred over the pipe with no data loss. This property is optional and it is only relevant when the value of getType() is one of SerialTypes.BackingType.PIPE_SERVER or SerialTypes.BackingType.PIPE_CLIENT.
        Parameters:
        noRxLoss - New value for the property.

      • getNetworkLocation

        public java.net.URI getNetworkLocation()
        URI specifying the location of the network service backing the virtual serial port.
        • If getType() is SerialTypes.BackingType.NETWORK_SERVER, this property is the location used by clients to connect to this server. The hostname part of the URI should either be empty or should specify the address of the host on which the virtual machine is running.
        • If getType() is SerialTypes.BackingType.NETWORK_CLIENT, this property is the location used by the virtual machine to connect to the remote server.
        This property is optional and it is only relevant when the value of getType() is one of SerialTypes.BackingType.NETWORK_SERVER or SerialTypes.BackingType.NETWORK_CLIENT.
        Returns:
        The current value of the property.
